'''José Pedro Balmaceda Pascal''' ({{IPA-es|xoˈse ˈpeðɾo βalmaˈseða pasˈkal|lang}}; born April 2, 1975) is a <!--Do not add any links, please see WP:OVERLINK.-->Chilean and American<!--No hyphen, as that may imply his ethnicity. This is about his nationalities.--> actor. After nearly two decades of taking small roles in film and television, Pascal had his [[breakthrough role|breakout role]] as [[Oberyn Martell]] in the [[Game of Thrones (season 4)|fourth season]] of the [[HBO]] fantasy series ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' (2014). He gained further prominence with his portrayal of [[Javier Peña]] in the [[Netflix]] crime series ''[[Narcos]]'' (2015–2017). He went on to appear in the films ''[[The Great Wall (film)|The Great Wall]]'' (2016), ''[[Kingsman: The Golden Circle]]'' (2017), ''[[The Equalizer 2]]'' (2018), and ''[[Triple Frontier (film)|Triple Frontier]]'' (2019).

Pascal's leading roles as [[The Mandalorian (character)|Din Djarin]] in the [[Disney+]] science fiction series ''[[The Mandalorian]]'' (2019–present) and [[Joel (The Last of Us)|Joel Miller]] in the HBO [[post-apocalyptic]] drama series ''[[The Last of Us (TV series)|The Last of Us]]'' (2023–present) propelled him to international stardom, and earned him a reputation for portraying adoptive [[father figure|father figures]].<ref>
<!--REPUTATION CITATIONS-->
*{{Cite web |last=Freitag |first=Lee |url=https://www.cbr.com/pedro-pascal-fans-compare-the-last-of-us-the-mandalorian/ |title=Pedro Pascal Fans Can't Stop Comparing The Last of Us and The Mandalorian |date=January 16, 2023 |website=[[Comic Book Resources|CBR]] |access-date=May 17, 2024 }}
<!---->
*{{Cite magazine |last=Ross |first=Dalton |url=https://ew.com/tv/pedro-pascal-grogu-ellie-last-of-us-mandalorian/ |title=Pedro Pascal says Grogu and Ellie from The Last of Us would be 'best friends' |date=March 8, 2023 |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |access-date=May 17, 2024 }}
<!---->
*{{Cite web |last=Coley |first=Samantha |url=https://collider.com/the-last-of-us-mandalorian-differences-pedro-pascal-comments/ |title='The Last of Us': Pedro Pascal on the Differences Between Joel and 'The Mandalorian's Din Djarin |date=January 7, 2023 |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |access-date=May 17, 2024 }}
<!---->
*{{Cite web |last=Phillips |first=Jordan |url=https://movieweb.com/ways-the-last-of-us-is-like-the-mandalorian/ |title=10 Ways The Last of Us is like The Mandalorian |date=January 26, 2023 |website=[[MovieWeb]] |access-date=May 17, 2024 }}</ref> For the latter, he received numerous accolades, including a [[Screen Actors Guild Award]] and a nomination for a [[Golden Globe Awards|Golden Globe Award]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/sag-awards-2024-snubs-surprises-barbie-succession-1235835269/|title=SAG Awards: Pedro Pascal and Elizabeth Debicki Surprise With Wins Over 'Succession' Stars as 'Barbie' Is Shut Out|last=Lewis|first=Hilary|date=24 February 2024|magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|access-date=25 February 2024|archive-date=February 25, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240225201638/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/sag-awards-2024-snubs-surprises-barbie-succession-1235835269/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Shanfeld |first=Ethan |date=December 11, 2023 |title=Golden Globes 2024: Full Nominations List (Updating Live) |url=https://variety.com/2023/film/news/golden-globes-nominations-list-nominees-2024-1235831576/ |access-date=December 11, 2023 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |language=en-US |archive-date=December 11, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231211132654/https://variety.com/2023/film/news/golden-globes-nominations-list-nominees-2024-1235831576/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Pascal's subsequent film roles were in ''[[Wonder Woman 1984]]'' (2020) and ''[[The Unbearable Weight of Massive Talent]]'' (2022). Active in theatre since 1999, he made his [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] debut as [[Edmund (King Lear)|Edmund]] in a 2019 adaptation of ''[[King Lear]]''.<ref name="debut">{{Cite web |last=Evans |first=Greg |url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/broadway-the-affair-ruth-wilson-game-of-thrones-pedro-pascal-glenda-jackson-king-lear-1202463090/ |title=Broadway: 'The Affair's Ruth Wilson, 'Game Of Thrones' Pedro Pascal On Board For Glenda Jackson's 'King Lear' |date=September 12, 2018 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]] |access-date=May 19, 2024}}</ref> ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine named him one of the [[Time 100|100 most influential people in the world]] in 2023.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://time.com/collection/100-most-influential-people-2023/ |title=Time 100 |magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |date=April 13, 2023 |access-date=April 13, 2023 |archive-date=April 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230413151502/https://time.com/collection/100-most-influential-people-2023/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Early life==
{{see also|Allende family|Balmaceda family}}

José Pedro Balmaceda Pascal was born on April 2, 1975, in [[Santiago]], [[Chile]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=Pedro Pascal Profile |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/celebrity/pedro_pascal |access-date= April 2, 2022 |agency=Rotten Tomatoes|archive-date= April 2, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220402214627/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/celebrity/pedro_pascal |url-status=live }}</ref> to child psychologist Verónica Pascal Ureta and fertility doctor José Balmaceda Riera.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ito |first=Robert |title=A Lethal Prince, Even if a Bit Clumsy: Pedro Pascal Becomes Red Viper on 'Game of Thrones' |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/30/arts/television/pedro-pascal-becomes-red-viper-on-game-of-thrones.html?_r=0 |access-date= May 27, 2014 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date= March 28, 2014 |archive-date= November 12, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112020115/http://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/30/arts/television/pedro-pascal-becomes-red-viper-on-game-of-thrones.html?_r=0 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="nytsarticle">{{cite web |last=Koblin |first=John |title=Pedro Pascal: Making It at 41 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/03/fashion/mens-style/pedro-pascal-great-wall-game-of-thrones-narcos-late-success.html |access-date= July 4, 2019 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date= February 3, 2017 |archive-date= December 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040531/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/03/fashion/mens-style/pedro-pascal-great-wall-game-of-thrones-narcos-late-success.html |url-status=live}}</ref> His paternal grandmother was born in [[Palma de Mallorca]], [[Spain]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Palma |first=Redacción |date=2017-09-21 |title=El pasado mallorquín del agente Peña de Narcos |url=https://www.diariodemallorca.es/sociedad/2017/09/21/pasado-mallorquin-agente-pena-narcos-3343743.html |access-date=2023-05-30 |website=Diario de Mallorca |language=es |archive-date=May 30, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230530210555/https://www.diariodemallorca.es/sociedad/2017/09/21/pasado-mallorquin-agente-pena-narcos-3343743.html |url-status=live }}</ref> He has an older sister named Javiera,<ref>{{cite web |title="Narcos" star Pedro Pascal on the mystery of Pablo Escobar's death | via=[[YouTube]] |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HC5G0bsSQtw |access-date= November 3, 2020 |archive-date= December 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040511/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HC5G0bsSQtw |url-status=live}}</ref> a younger brother named Nicolás,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Pascal |first=Pedro |date=April 10, 2019 |title=This is my brother, Nicolas. |url=https://www.instagram.com/accounts/login/?next=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FBwE8pfHDb4Y%2F%3Fhl%3Den |access-date=2023-07-09 |website=www.instagram.com}}</ref> and a younger sister named [[Lux Pascal|Lux]], who is an actress and [[transgender]] activist.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.t13.cl/noticia/entretencion/Lucas-Balmaceda-el-hermano-del-chileno-de-Game-of-Thrones-que-llego-a-remecer-Los-80 |title=Lucas Balmaceda, el hermano del chileno de Game of Thrones que llegó a remecer Los 80 |website=t13.cl |date=November 12, 2014 |access-date= January 13, 2018 |archive-date= November 11, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111204523/https://www.t13.cl/noticia/entretencion/Lucas-Balmaceda-el-hermano-del-chileno-de-Game-of-Thrones-que-llego-a-remecer-Los-80 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Pedro Pascal Sweetly Supports His Sister Lux After She Comes Out as a Trans Woman: 'Mi Corazón' |url=https://people.com/movies/pedro-pascal-supports-sister-lux-comes-out-trans-woman/ |website=People |date= February 9, 2021 |access-date= February 12, 2021 |archive-date= February 11, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211212045/https://people.com/movies/pedro-pascal-supports-sister-lux-comes-out-trans-woman/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Pascal's mother was the cousin of [[Andrés Pascal Allende]], the nephew of socialist [[President of Chile|Chilean President]] [[Salvador Allende]] (through his sister [[Laura Allende|Laura]]). Pascal Allende was an early leader of the [[Revolutionary Left Movement (Chile)|Movement of the Revolutionary Left]], a militant [[far-left]] organization.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.latercera.com/noticia/pedro-pascal-punto/ |title=Pedro Pascal, en su punto |website=La Tercera |date=  September 1, 2017 |access-date= January 10, 2021 |archive-date= February 24, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224073623/https://www.latercera.com/noticia/pedro-pascal-punto/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Nine months after his birth, his family sought refuge in the [[Venezuela]]n embassy in Santiago, and later received political asylum in [[Denmark]].<ref name="people">{{cite web |date=November 13, 2020 |title=The Mandalorian's Pedro Pascal Credits His Success to His Mom, Who Died Before He Became Famous |url=https://people.com/tv/the-mandalorian-pedro-pascal-credits-his-success-to-his-mom/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201212035519/https://people.com/tv/the-mandalorian-pedro-pascal-credits-his-success-to-his-mom/ |archive-date=December 12, 2020 |access-date=January 1, 2021 |website=People}}</ref><ref name=OrangeCoast>{{cite news |last=Broeske |first=Pat H. |title=The Viper Prince |url=http://www.orangecoast.com/features/2014/04/28/the-viper-prince |access-date= May 27, 2014 |publisher=Orange Coast |date= April 28, 2014 |archive-date= June 2, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140602035249/http://www.orangecoast.com/features/2014/04/28/the-viper-prince |url-status=live}}</ref> Ultimately, the family moved to the United States, where Pascal was raised in [[San Antonio, Texas]],<ref>{{cite news |last=McIntyre |first=Gina |title='Game of Thrones': Red Viper actor Pedro Pascal hates spoilers too |url=http://herocomplex.latimes.com/tv/game-of-thrones-red-viper-actor-pedro-pascal-hates-spoilers-too/ |access-date= May 27, 2014 |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date= May 12, 2014 |archive-date= September 8, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908015642/https://herocomplex.latimes.com/tv/game-of-thrones-red-viper-actor-pedro-pascal-hates-spoilers-too/ }}</ref> until they relocated to [[Orange County, California]], when he was 11 years old.<ref name=OrangeCoast/> By the time he was eight years old, his family regularly visited Chile to see his 34 cousins.<ref name="variety">{{cite magazine |last=Vary |first=Adam B. |title=Pedro Pascal on Fame and 'The Mandalorian': 'Can We Cut the S— and Talk About the Child?' |url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/pedro-pascal-the-mandalorian-star-wars-wonder-woman-1984-1234803468/ |access-date= January 1, 2021 |magazine=Variety |date= October 14, 2020 |archive-date= October 15, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201015194622/https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/pedro-pascal-the-mandalorian-star-wars-wonder-woman-1984-1234803468/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

He pursued acting at the [[Orange County School of the Arts]] and graduated in 1993, before attending [[New York University]]'s [[Tisch School of the Arts]], where he graduated in 1997.<ref name=OrangeCoast/><ref name="ETW">{{cite web |title=ETW Alumni |url=https://tisch.nyu.edu/drama/about/studios/experimental-theatre-wing/alumni |website=[[New York University]] |access-date= January 1, 2021 |archive-date= January 19, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210119205137/https://tisch.nyu.edu/drama/about/studios/experimental-theatre-wing/alumni |url-status=live }}</ref> After his mother's death, he began using her surname professionally as a tribute to her and because he felt that Americans had difficulty pronouncing his paternal surname, Balmaceda.<ref name="variety" />

== Career ==

=== 1999–2013: Early work ===
Pascal has appeared in several television series, including ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]'', ''[[The Good Wife]]'', ''[[Homeland (TV series)|Homeland]]'', ''[[The Mentalist]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]], [[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]],'' and ''[[Graceland (TV series)|Graceland]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title=''The Good Wife'' Actor Checks Into USA's ''Graceland'' in Major Arc |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/graceland-pedro-pascal-joins-386618 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |last=Ng |first=Philiana |access-date= May 30, 2013 |date= November 5, 2012 |archive-date= December 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040507/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/graceland-pedro-pascal-joins-386618 |url-status=live}}</ref> He was cast in the [[Pilot (tv)|pilot]] for the [[Wonder Woman (2011 TV pilot)|2011 ''Wonder Woman'' television adaptation]], but the show was not picked up.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Guthrie |first=Marisa |date= March 3, 2011 |title=Pedro Pascal Joins NBC's 'Wonder Woman' Pilot |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/pedro-pascal-joins-nbcs-wonder-164014/ |access-date= July 18, 2021 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |language=en-US |archive-date= July 18, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210718145651/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/pedro-pascal-joins-nbcs-wonder-164014/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://ew.com/tv/pedro-pascal-wonder-woman-pilot/ |title=Pedro Pascal briefly forgot he was in NBC's 'very risky' 'Wonder Woman' pilot |date=December 29, 2020 |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |access-date=April 7, 2023 |archive-date=April 7, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230407053606/https://ew.com/tv/pedro-pascal-wonder-woman-pilot/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

[[File:Pedro Pascal SDCC 2014.jpg|thumb|upright|Pascal at the 2014 [[San Diego Comic Con]]]]

Pascal has extensive stage experience as both an actor and director; he received the Los Angeles Drama Critics Circle Award and [[Back Stage Garland Awards|Garland Award]] for his role in the [[International City Theater]] production of ''Orphans'', and has performed in classical and contemporary works.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.broadway.com/buzz/stars/pedro-pascal/profile/ |title=Star File – Pedro Pascal |website=broadway.com |access-date=May 20, 2024 }}</ref> In 2010, he wrote a play, directed by [[Sarah Silverman]], ''Flaca Loves Bone'', about four siblings who meet in a snowy wood to uncover a family secret.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Pedro Pascal |url=https://www.doollee.com/PlaywrightsP/pascal-pedro.php |access-date= February 26, 2023 |website=www.doollee.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221210015015/https://www.doollee.com/PlaywrightsP/pascal-pedro.php |archive-date= December 10, 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> He made his directorial debut with play ''underneathmybed'' in 2008. He also directed ''Yosemite'' and ''Killing Play'' at [[Rattlestick Playwrights Theater]].<ref>{{Cite web |date= December 15, 2011 |title=RATTLESTICK PLAYWRIGHTS THEATER to present World Premiere of "YOSEMITE" by Daniel Talbott |url=https://www.omdkc.com/rattlestick-playwrights-theater-to-present-world-premiere-of-yosemite-by-da/ |access-date= February 26, 2023 |website=DKC/O&M |language=en-US |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171231201948/https://www.omdkc.com/rattlestick-playwrights-theater-to-present-world-premiere-of-yosemite-by-da/ |archive-date= December 31, 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |author=BWW News Desk |title=Rattlestick Playwrights' underneathmybed Closes 10/10 |url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/off-broadway/article/Rattlestick-Playwrights-underneathmybed-Closes-1010-20101010 |access-date= February 26, 2023 |website=BroadwayWorld.com |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226145858/https://www.broadwayworld.com/off-broadway/article/Rattlestick-Playwrights-underneathmybed-Closes-1010-20101010 |archive-date=  February 26, 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> He is a member of New York City's [[LAByrinth Theater Company]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Company Members |url=http://www.labtheater.org/companymembers/memberslist.html |website=[[LAByrinth Theater Company]] |access-date= June 4, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019045129/http://www.labtheater.org/companymembers/memberslist.html |archive-date= October 19, 2013}}</ref>

=== 2014–2022: Breakthrough ===
In 2014, Pascal portrayed the character [[Oberyn Martell]] in the [[Game of Thrones (season 4)|fourth season]] of the [[HBO]]'s critically acclaimed television series ''[[Game of Thrones]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Wolff |first=Natasha |date=2014-04-02 |title=Pedro Pascal Joins Game of Thrones as the Red Viper and Had "Nerd Moments," Furious About Spoilers |url=https://dujour.com/culture/pedro-pascal-red-viper-game-of-thrones/ |access-date=2023-07-13 |website=DuJour |language=en-US |archive-date=July 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230713204031/https://dujour.com/culture/pedro-pascal-red-viper-game-of-thrones/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The season aired from April 6 to June 15, 2014, and Pascal's performance as the passionate and vengeful Prince of Dorne garnered significant praise from both critics and audiences.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Game of Thrones already lost its greatest hero: Why I loved Oberyn Martell |url=https://www.cnet.com/culture/entertainment/game-of-thrones-already-lost-its-greatest-hero-oberyn-martell/ |access-date=2023-07-13 |website=CNET |language=en |archive-date=July 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230713204031/https://www.cnet.com/culture/entertainment/game-of-thrones-already-lost-its-greatest-hero-oberyn-martell/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Pascal stated that he was a huge fan of the show before being cast as Oberyn and was ecstatic to join.<ref name="reddit">{{Cite web |last=Pedro_Pascal |date=2014-05-25 |title=I am actor Pedro Pascal. I play Oberyn in Game of Thrones, Ask me anything. |url=http://www.reddit.com/r/IAmA/comments/26gtvt/i_am_actor_pedro_pascal_i_play_oberyn_in_game_of/ |access-date=2023-07-09 |website=r/IAmA |archive-date=July 20, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230720014550/https://www.reddit.com/r/IAmA/comments/26gtvt/i_am_actor_pedro_pascal_i_play_oberyn_in_game_of/ |url-status=live }}</ref> As part of the ensemble, he has received a [[Screen Actors Guild Awards]] nomination for [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series|Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series]].<ref>{{Cite web |author=T. H. R. Staff |date=2015-01-24 |title=SAG Awards: Complete List of Winners |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/general-news/sag-awards-2015-winners-list-765943/ |access-date=2023-07-12 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |language=en-US |archive-date=January 25, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220125043436/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/general-news/sag-awards-2015-winners-list-765943/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In the 2015 movie, ''[[Bloodsucking Bastards]]'', Pascal portrayed the [[vampire]] Max.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Miska |first1=Brad |title=INDIE'Bloodsucking Bastards' Turns Cast Into Vamps |url=https://bloody-disgusting.com/indie/3289705/bloodsucking-bastards-turns-cast-into-vamps/ |date= April 21, 2014 |website=bloody-disgusting.com |access-date= June 7, 2017 |archive-date= December 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040442/https://bloody-disgusting.com/indie/3289705/bloodsucking-bastards-turns-cast-into-vamps/ |url-status=live}}</ref> In April 2015, Pascal co-starred with [[Heidi Klum]] in the music video for [[Sia]]'s "[[Fire Meet Gasoline]]".<ref name=":5">{{cite web |last1=Gordon |first1=Jeremy |title=Sia's "Fire Meet Gasoline" Used in Video Starring Heidi Klum, "Game of Thrones" Actor Pedro Pascal |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/59388-sias-fire-meet-gasoline-used-in-video-starring-heidi-klum-game-of-thrones-actor-pedro-pascal/ |website=[[Pitchfork Media]] |access-date= April 23, 2015 |date=  April 23, 2015 |archive-date= December 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040539/https://pitchfork.com/news/59388-sias-fire-meet-gasoline-used-in-video-starring-heidi-klum-game-of-thrones-actor-pedro-pascal/ |url-status=live}}</ref> In August 2015, Pascal gained further recognition for his portrayal as [[Javier Peña]], based on a real-life [[Drug Enforcement Administration|DEA agent]], in the popular [[Netflix]] crime drama series ''[[Narcos]]''. The show's two first seasons depict the rise and fall of the infamous drug lord [[Pablo Escobar]] and the subsequent [[Medellín Cartel]], as the show's focus shifted to the [[Cali Cartel]] for its [[Narcos (season 3)|third]] and final season, Pascal took on the role of both lead actor and narrator.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=2014-06-06 |title=Pedro Pascal To Star In Netflix Drama Series 'Narcos' |url=https://deadline.com/2014/06/pedro-pascal-stars-narcos-netflix-741258/ |access-date=2023-07-12 |website=Deadline |language=en-US |archive-date=July 9, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230709205815/https://deadline.com/2014/06/pedro-pascal-stars-narcos-netflix-741258/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Strause |first=Jackie |date=2017-08-31 |title='Narcos' Star Pedro Pascal on Returning for a More "Insidious" Season 3 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/narcos-season-3-pedro-pascal-interview-1033514/ |access-date=2023-07-12 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |language=en-US |archive-date=July 12, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230712215935/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/narcos-season-3-pedro-pascal-interview-1033514/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In 2016, he portrayed mercenary Pero Tovar in the fantasy action film ''[[The Great Wall (film)|The Great Wall]],'' alongside [[Matt Damon]], and directed by [[Zhang Yimou]].<ref>{{Cite web |date= February 15, 2017 |title=Pedro Pascal goes from 'Game of Thrones' to 'Great Wall' |url=https://www.dailynews.com/arts-and-entertainment/20170215/pedro-pascal-goes-from-game-of-thrones-to-great-wall |access-date= May 26, 2022 |website=Daily News |language=en-US |archive-date= May 15, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170515170352/http://www.dailynews.com/arts-and-entertainment/20170215/pedro-pascal-goes-from-game-of-thrones-to-great-wall |url-status=live }}</ref> Set against the backdrop of the iconic [[Great Wall of China]], the film follows European mercenaries who become embroiled in a battle against ancient creatures threatening humanity. Despite the film's visually stunning production and ambitious scope, it received mixed reviews for its narrative and character development.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Roxburgh |first=Helen |date=2016-12-16 |title=The Great Wall review – Matt Damon epic delivers spectacle but not soul |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/dec/16/the-great-wall-review-matt-damon-zhang-yimou |access-date=2024-01-06 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077 |archive-date=November 7, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231107105545/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/dec/16/the-great-wall-review-matt-damon-zhang-yimou |url-status=live }}</ref> Filmed on location in [[Qingdao]], [[China]].<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Barnes |first1=Brooks |last2=Qin |first2=Amy |date=2016-12-21 |title=The East Lobs a Blockbuster-Hopeful to the West With 'The Great Wall' |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/21/movies/the-great-wall-china-film-industry.html |access-date=2024-01-06 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=April 9, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230409235034/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/21/movies/the-great-wall-china-film-industry.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Pascal has voiced his admiration for Yimou, whom he had been a fan of during his youth.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-02-16 |title=Chinese Film Buff Pedro Pascal Opens Up On The Great Wall |url=http://www.traileraddict.com/article/chinese-film-buff-pedro-pascal-opens-great-wall/ |access-date=2024-01-06 |website=Trailer Addict |language=en-US |archive-date=January 6, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240106213129/https://www.traileraddict.com/article/chinese-film-buff-pedro-pascal-opens-great-wall/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In 2017, Pascal portrayed the charismatic and skilled operative within the Statesman organization, Jack Daniels, also known as Agent Whiskey, in [[Matthew Vaughn]]'s ''[[Kingsman: The Golden Circle]].''<ref>{{Cite web |last=Jaafar |first=Ali |date=2016-04-08 |title='Games Of Thrones' Pedro Pascal To Board 'Kingsman: The Golden Circle' |url=https://deadline.com/2016/04/games-of-thrones-pedro-pascal-kingsman-2-narcos-netflix-halle-berry-julianne-moore-matt-damon-great-wall-china-1201725794/ |access-date=2023-07-09 |website=Deadline |language=en-US |archive-date=December 10, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201210190801/https://deadline.com/2016/04/games-of-thrones-pedro-pascal-kingsman-2-narcos-netflix-halle-berry-julianne-moore-matt-damon-great-wall-china-1201725794/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In 2018, he starred as Dave York, the main antagonist, in [[Denzel Washington]]'s thriller sequel film ''[[The Equalizer 2]]''.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ford |first1=Rebecca |title='The Equalizer' Sequel Adds Pedro Pascal |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/equalizer-sequel-adds-pedro-pascal-1030230 |access-date= August 22, 2017 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date= August 21, 2017 |archive-date= August 24, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170824092247/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/equalizer-sequel-adds-pedro-pascal-1030230 |url-status=live }}</ref>  In ''[[Prospect (film)|Prospect]]'', Pascal portrayed the character Ezra, a seasoned and enigmatic prospector navigating a dangerous alien moon in search of valuable resources. In 2018's [[If Beale Street Could Talk (film)|''If Beale Street Could Talk'']], directed by [[Barry Jenkins]] and based on [[James Baldwin]]'s novel, Pascal made a cameo appearance as Pietro Alvarez, a frivolous yet crucial character who ultimately reveals a compassionate and empathetic side.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Light |first=Jo |url=https://collider.com/pedro-pascal-if-beale-street-could-talk/ |title=Pedro Pascal Gave Us His All in This Uncredited Role |date=March 23, 2023 |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |access-date=May 20, 2024 }}</ref>

In February 2019, Pascal made his [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] debut in an adaptation of ''[[King Lear]]'' with [[Glenda Jackson]] and [[Ruth Wilson]], where he took on the role of [[Edmund (King Lear)|Edmund]], the cunning and ambitious illegitimate son of the [[Robert, 1st Earl of Gloucester|Earl of Gloucester]].<ref>{{Cite web |last1=12 September |first1=David Canfield |last2=EDT |first2=2018 at 10:31 AM |title=Ruth Wilson, Pedro Pascal, more to star opposite Glenda Jackson in 'King Lear' on Broadway |url=https://ew.com/theater/2018/09/12/ruth-wilson-pedro-pascal-king-lear/ |access-date= April 15, 2022 |website=EW.com |language=en |archive-date= April 15, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220415193039/https://ew.com/theater/2018/09/12/ruth-wilson-pedro-pascal-king-lear/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Since 2019, Pascal has portrayed the [[The Mandalorian (character)|title role]] in ''[[The Mandalorian]]'', the first live-action ''[[Star Wars]]'' television series, which debuted on [[Disney+]], the show follows the adventures of a lone [[bounty hunter]] in the outer reaches of the galaxy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/the-mandalorian-star-wars-pedro-pascal-talks-disney-streaming-series-1202501235/ |title='The Mandalorian' Targets Pedro Pascal For Title Role In Disney+ Series |last=Boucher |first=Geoff |website=Deadline |date= November 13, 2018 |access-date= November 14, 2018 |archive-date= November 13, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113232557/https://deadline.com/2018/11/the-mandalorian-star-wars-pedro-pascal-talks-disney-streaming-series-1202501235/ |url-status=live}}</ref> The same year, he starred as Francisco "Catfish" Morales in the [[Netflix]] heist drama ''[[Triple Frontier (film)|Triple Frontier]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Fleming |first=Mike Jr. |date=2018-03-19 |title='Triple Frontier' Finally Going: Affleck, Isaac, Pascal, Hunnam, Hedlund, Arjona In JC Chandor's Lineup |url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/triple-frontier-movie-ben-affleck-oscar-isaac-pedro-pascal-charlie-hunnam-garrett-hedlund-adria-arjona-jc-chandor-netflix-1202345230/ |access-date=2023-07-09 |website=Deadline |language=en-US |archive-date=March 24, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180324191245/https://deadline.com/2018/03/triple-frontier-movie-ben-affleck-oscar-isaac-pedro-pascal-charlie-hunnam-garrett-hedlund-adria-arjona-jc-chandor-netflix-1202345230/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

He portrayed [[Maxwell Lord]] in the [[DC Extended Universe]] film ''[[Wonder Woman 1984]]'', directed by [[Patty Jenkins]]. Following delays due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]], the film was released to theaters and [[HBO Max]] on December 25, 2020.<ref name="PascalCast">{{cite news |last1=Kroll |first1=Justin |date=March 28, 2018 |title='Narcos' Star Pedro Pascal Lands Key Role in 'Wonder Woman' Sequel (EXCLUSIVE) |work=Variety |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/pedro-pascal-wonder-woman-sequel-narcos-1202738657/ |url-status=live |access-date=May 29, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180329010138/http://variety.com/2018/film/news/pedro-pascal-wonder-woman-sequel-narcos-1202738657/ |archive-date=March 29, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Rubin |first=Rebecca |date=2020-11-18 |title='Wonder Woman 1984' to Debut Both on HBO Max and in Theaters |url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/wonder-woman-1984-hbo-max-release-1234804411/ |access-date=2023-07-09 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=November 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201118233910/https://variety.com/2020/film/news/wonder-woman-1984-hbo-max-release-1234804411/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In early 2021, a video from a 2020 virtual play reading surfaced on multiple social media platforms of Pascal laughing hysterically then transitioning smoothly into crying.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Conlin |first=Dan |date=2021-10-27 |title=Pedro Pascal Has Become A Meme Thanks To This Script Read Over Zoom |url=https://gamerant.com/pedro-pascal-meme-script-read-zoom/ |access-date=2024-03-26 |website=Game Rant |language=en |archive-date=December 21, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211221214307/https://gamerant.com/pedro-pascal-meme-script-read-zoom/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-03-31 |title=Why the Internet is Still Obsessed With Pedro Pascal Memes |url=https://whatstrending.com/why-the-internet-is-still-obsessed-with-pedro-pascal-memes/ |access-date=2024-03-26 |website=What's Trending |language=en-US |archive-date=March 26, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240326231755/https://whatstrending.com/why-the-internet-is-still-obsessed-with-pedro-pascal-memes/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The video quickly became an [[internet meme]], often being paired with the [[Beach House]] song "[[Space Song]]" to display themes of tragedy on social media.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-02-16 |title=Beach House Are Still Surprising Each Other |url=https://pitchfork.com/features/interview/beach-house-once-twice-melody/ |access-date=2024-03-26 |website=Pitchfork |language=en-US |archive-date=June 3, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230603042202/https://pitchfork.com/features/interview/beach-house-once-twice-melody/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Pedro Pascal Crying Meme |url=https://www.tiktok.com/channel/pedro-pascal-crying-meme?lang=en |access-date=2024-03-26 |website=TikTok |language=en |archive-date=March 26, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240326231754/https://www.tiktok.com/channel/pedro-pascal-crying-meme?lang=en |url-status=live }}</ref>

In 2022, Pascal co-starred with [[Nicolas Cage]] in the [[action comedy]] film ''[[The Unbearable Weight of Massive Talent]].'' His performance was widely praised by the critics.<ref>{{Cite web |last=DeFore |first=John |date= March 13, 2022 |title=Nicolas Cage in 'The Unbearable Weight of Massive Talent': Film Review {{!}} SXSW 2022 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/nicolas-cage-in-the-unbearable-weight-of-massive-talent-film-sxsw-2022-1235110212/ |access-date= April 15, 2022 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |language=en-US |archive-date= April 15, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220415191536/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/nicolas-cage-in-the-unbearable-weight-of-massive-talent-film-sxsw-2022-1235110212/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=DeFore |first=John |date=2022-03-13 |title=Nicolas Cage in 'The Unbearable Weight of Massive Talent': Film Review {{!}} SXSW 2022 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/nicolas-cage-in-the-unbearable-weight-of-massive-talent-film-sxsw-2022-1235110212/ |access-date=2023-07-13 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |language=en-US |archive-date=April 15, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220415191536/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/nicolas-cage-in-the-unbearable-weight-of-massive-talent-film-sxsw-2022-1235110212/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Pascal also appeared in [[The Bubble (2022 film)|''The Bubble'']], [[Judd Apatow]]'s [[satirical]] comedy exploring [[celebrity culture]] amidst the pandemic.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rooney |first=David |date=2022-04-01 |title=Judd Apatow's 'The Bubble': Film Review |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/the-bubble-judd-apatow-netflix-1235122165/ |access-date=2023-07-13 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |language=en-US |archive-date=July 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230713204031/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/the-bubble-judd-apatow-netflix-1235122165/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He starred in [[Miu Miu]]'s [[Women's Tales]]' series short film, directed by [[Janicza Bravo]], titled ''House Comes With a Bird''.<ref>{{Cite web |title=MIU MIU WOMEN'S TALES SHORT FILM: 'HOUSE COMES WITH A BIRD' - CRASH Magazine |url=https://www.crash.fr/miu-miu-womens-tales-short-film-house-comes-with-a-bird/ |access-date=2023-07-13 |website=www.crash.fr |archive-date=July 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230713204032/https://www.crash.fr/miu-miu-womens-tales-short-film-house-comes-with-a-bird/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In November 2022, he was cast in ''[[Freaky Tales (film)|Freaky Tales]]'', directed by [[Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kroll |first1=Justin |title=Pedro Pascal, Ben Mendelsohn, Jay Ellis And Jack Champion Among Those Joining Ensemble Of eOne And Macro's ''Freaky Tales'' From Ryan Fleck And Anna Boden |url=https://deadline.com/2022/11/pedro-pascal-ben-mendelsoh-jay-ellis-jack-champion-eone-macros-freaky-tales-ryan-fleck-anna-boden-1235174116/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date= November 16, 2022 |date= November 16, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221116203809/https://deadline.com/2022/11/pedro-pascal-ben-mendelsoh-jay-ellis-jack-champion-eone-macros-freaky-tales-ryan-fleck-anna-boden-1235174116/ |archive-date= November 16, 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== 2023–present: Worldwide recognition ===
In 2023, Pascal starred in the [[HBO]]'s highly anticipated television adaptation, [[The Last of Us (TV series)|''The Last of Us'']], based on the critically acclaimed video game under the [[The Last of Us|same title]], created by [[Craig Mazin]] and [[Neil Druckmann]].<ref name="Deadline Pascal">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2021/02/pedro-pascal-star-joel-the-last-of-us-hbo-series-video-game-playstation-1234691935/ |title=Pedro Pascal To Star As Joel In 'The Last of Us' HBO Series Based On Video Game |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |date=February 10, 2021 |access-date=February 11, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211034813/https://deadline.com/2021/02/pedro-pascal-star-joel-the-last-of-us-hbo-series-video-game-playstation-1234691935/ |archive-date= February 11, 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref> He took on the role of [[Joel (The Last of Us)|Joel Miller]], a hardened survivor in a [[Apocalyptic and post-apocalyptic fiction|post-apocalyptic]] world, tasked with protecting a young girl named [[Ellie (The Last of Us)|Ellie]], played by [[Bella Ramsey]]. Pascal reportedly received $600,000 per episode.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Otterson |first1=Michael Schneider,Joe |last2=Schneider |first2=Michael |last3=Otterson |first3=Joe |date= August 18, 2021 |title=Streaming Boom Keeps TV Salaries at Heady Levels: Here's What Kate Winslet, Jason Sudeikis and More Are Earning |url=https://variety.com/2021/tv/news/tv-salaries-2021-kate-winslet-jason-sudeikis-succession-1235043291/ |access-date= April 15, 2022 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date= August 18, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210818232156/https://variety.com/2021/tv/news/tv-salaries-2021-kate-winslet-jason-sudeikis-succession-1235043291/ |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Empire (magazine)|Empire]]''<nowiki/>'s [[John Nugent (journalist)|John Nugent]] and ''[[/Film]]''<nowiki/>'s Valerie Ettenhofer praised Pascal's performance as the best of his career, citing his ability to portray nuance and rare vulnerability.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023 |title=The Last Of Us |url=https://www.empireonline.com/tv/reviews/the-last-of-us/ |access-date=2023-07-13 |website=Empire |archive-date=January 10, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230110165149/https://www.empireonline.com/tv/reviews/the-last-of-us/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-10 |title=The Last Of Us Review: A Thrilling, Character-Driven Achievement For Game Fans And Newcomers Alike |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/1160701/the-last-of-us-review-a-thrilling-character-driven-achievement-for-game-fans-and-newcomers-alike/ |access-date=2023-07-13 |website=/Film |language=en-US |archive-date=January 10, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230110164510/https://www.slashfilm.com/1160701/the-last-of-us-review-a-thrilling-character-driven-achievement-for-game-fans-and-newcomers-alike/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In February, he hosted a ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' episode, with [[Coldplay]] as the musical guest.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Vasquez |first=Zach |date=2023-02-05 |title=Saturday Night Live: Pedro Pascal makes a promising debut as host |language=en-GB |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/feb/05/saturday-night-live-pedro-pascal-host |access-date=2023-07-13 |issn=0261-3077 |archive-date=July 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230713204031/https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/feb/05/saturday-night-live-pedro-pascal-host |url-status=live }}</ref> In April, he was added to the cast of [[Ethan Coen]]'s ''[[Drive-Away Dolls]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=D'Alessandro |first1=Anthony |title=Ethan Coen's Margaret Qualley & Geraldine Viswanathan ''Drive-Away Dolls'' To Park At Cinemas This Fall |url=https://deadline.com/2023/04/margaret-qualley-ethan-coen-drive-away-dolls-theatrical-release-date-1235328531/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date= April 17, 2023 |date= April 17, 2023 |archive-date= April 17, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230417184232/https://deadline.com/2023/04/margaret-qualley-ethan-coen-drive-away-dolls-theatrical-release-date-1235328531/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In May, he co-starred in the short film ''[[Strange Way of Life]]'' alongside [[Ethan Hawke]], directed by [[Pedro Almodóvar]], whom Pascal has previously expressed his admiration for and desire to work with.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hopewell |first=John |date=2022-06-28 |title=Ethan Hawke, Pedro Pascal to Star in Pedro Almodovar's Western 'Strange Way of Life' |url=https://variety.com/2022/film/news/ethan-hawke-pedro-almodovar-pedro-pascal-1235304937/ |access-date=2023-07-13 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=April 22, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230422011008/https://variety.com/2022/film/news/ethan-hawke-pedro-almodovar-pedro-pascal-1235304937/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Citation |title=Pedro Pascal from Narcos wants to work with Pedro Almodóvar. |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MWqfamcNl-E |access-date=2023-07-13 |language=en |archive-date=July 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230713204031/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MWqfamcNl-E |url-status=live }}</ref> In May, Pascal was cast in ''[[Gladiator II]]'', the upcoming sequel of [[Ridley Scott]]'s ''[[Gladiator (2000 film)|Gladiator]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date=2023-05-01 |title=Pedro Pascal Joins Ridley Scott's 'Gladiator' Sequel At Paramount |url=https://deadline.com/2023/05/pedro-pascal-ridley-scotts-gladiator-paramount-1235352214/ |access-date=2023-05-28 |website=Deadline |language=en-US |archive-date=June 21, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230621075529/https://deadline.com/2023/05/pedro-pascal-ridley-scotts-gladiator-paramount-1235352214/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-05-26 |title="Esto se va a descontrolar": Almodóvar adelantó que Pedro Pascal "está con dieta rigurosa y ejercicios brutales para conseguir cuerpo del gladiador" |url=https://www.publimetro.cl/entretenimiento/2023/05/26/esto-se-va-a-descontrolar-almodovar-adelanto-que-pedro-pascal-esta-con-dieta-rigurosa-y-ejercicios-brutales-para-conseguir-cuerpo-del-gladiador/ |access-date=2023-05-28 |website=Publimetro Chile |language=es |archive-date=May 28, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230528141117/https://www.publimetro.cl/entretenimiento/2023/05/26/esto-se-va-a-descontrolar-almodovar-adelanto-que-pedro-pascal-esta-con-dieta-rigurosa-y-ejercicios-brutales-para-conseguir-cuerpo-del-gladiador/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In June, Pascal was named by [[Carnegie Corporation of New York]] as an honoree of the [[Great Immigrants Award]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://apnews.com/article/pedro-pascal-ajay-banga-carnegie-great-immigrants-f28abf588332dd3bf2fe089100efb279|title=Pedro Pascal and World Bank’s Ajay Banga among those named to Carnegie’s 2023 Great Immigrants list|last=Gamboa|first=Glenn|date=June 28, 2023|agency=[[Associated Press News]]|access-date=February 16, 2024|archive-date=February 16, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240216153731/https://apnews.com/article/pedro-pascal-ajay-banga-carnegie-great-immigrants-f28abf588332dd3bf2fe089100efb279|url-status=live}}</ref> In July, Pascal made history as the first Latino to receive three nominations in the same year for the [[75th Primetime Emmy Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Davis |first=Clayton |date=2023-07-12 |title=Emmys Diversity Report: Pedro Pascal Makes Latino History, Black Women Set Acting Record |url=https://variety.com/2023/tv/awards/2023-emmys-diversity-pedro-pascal-jenna-ortega-quinta-brunson-1235667840/ |access-date=2023-07-12 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=July 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230713012630/https://variety.com/2023/tv/awards/2023-emmys-diversity-pedro-pascal-jenna-ortega-quinta-brunson-1235667840/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The nominations included [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actor in a Drama Series|Outstanding Lead Actor in a Drama Series]] for his portrayal in ''The Last of Us'', [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Guest Actor in a Comedy Series|Outstanding Guest Actor in a Comedy Series]] for his guest-hosting role in an episode of ''Saturday Night Live'', and [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Narrator|Outstanding Narrator]] for his narration in ''Patagonia: Life on the Edge of the World''.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Sherman |first=Rachel |date=2023-07-12 |title=Emmy Nominees 2023: The Complete List |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2023/07/12/arts/television/emmy-nominees-list-2023.html |access-date=2023-07-12 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=September 8, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230908030753/https://www.nytimes.com/2023/07/12/arts/television/emmy-nominees-list-2023.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

In February 2024, Pascal was cast as [[Reed Richards|Reed Richards / Mister Fantastic]] in the  [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] film ''[[The Fantastic Four (2025 film)|The Fantastic Four]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Vary|first1=Adam B.|url=https://variety.com/2024/film/news/fantastic-four-cast-marvel-studios-1235875766/|title=Marvel’s ‘The Fantastic Four’ Lands Its Cast: Pedro Pascal, Vanessa Kirby, Joseph Quinn, Ebon Moss-Bachrach|date=February 14, 2024|publisher=Variety|access-date=February 14, 2024|archive-date=February 14, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240214172146/https://variety.com/2024/film/news/fantastic-four-cast-marvel-studios-1235875766/|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Pascal is fluent in both English and Spanish and has been a resident of [[New York City]] since 1993.<ref name=OrangeCoast/> He developed a close friendship with actress [[Sarah Paulson]] soon after moving there.<ref name=Interview>{{cite web |url=https://www.interviewmagazine.com/culture/pedro-pascal |title=Pedro Pascal |author=Sarah Paulson |author-link=Sarah Paulson |date= September 18, 2014 |access-date= February 11, 2021 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116150127/https://www.interviewmagazine.com/culture/pedro-pascal |archive-date= January 16, 2021}}</ref>

Pascal is an advocate of [[LGBT rights by country or territory|LGBTQ+ rights]]<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ennis |first=Dawn |title=This Is The Way 'The Mandalorian' Cast Gets Personal On Social Media |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dawnstaceyennis/2020/10/30/this-is-the-way-the-mandalorian-cast-gets-personal-on-social-media/ |access-date= April 10, 2022 |website=Forbes |language=en |archive-date= April 11, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220411001948/https://www.forbes.com/sites/dawnstaceyennis/2020/10/30/this-is-the-way-the-mandalorian-cast-gets-personal-on-social-media/ |url-status=live }}</ref> and was supportive of his sister [[Lux Pascal]] when she came out as [[transgender]]. Lux said, "He has been an important part of this. He is also an artist and has been a guide. He was one of the first to give me the things that formed my identity."<ref>{{Cite web |date= February 10, 2021 |title=Pedro Pascal Sends Love To Sister Coming Out As Transgender |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/pedro-pascal-sister-coming-out-as-transgender_n_6023eac3c5b6d78d444b623e |access-date= April 11, 2022 |website=HuffPost |language=en |archive-date= April 11, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220411002729/https://www.huffpost.com/entry/pedro-pascal-sister-coming-out-as-transgender_n_6023eac3c5b6d78d444b623e |url-status=live }}</ref>

Pascal identifies as an [[Agnosticism|agnostic]] and a [[Progressive liberals|progressive liberal]].<ref>{{Cite journal |date= February 23, 2017 |title=Bad Hombre Pedro Pascal |journal=Solar Magazine}}</ref> He endorsed leftist [[Gabriel Boric]] in the [[2021 Chilean presidential election]].<ref>{{Cite web |date= November 23, 2021 |title=Pedro Pascal hace público con una fotografía su apoyo a Gabriel Boric |url=https://www.t13.cl/noticia/elecciones-2021/tendencias/pedro-pascal-apoyo-gabriel-boric-elecciones-segunda-vuelta-23-11-2021 |last= |first= |access-date= November 29, 2021 |work=[[Teletrece]] |archive-date= November 29, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211129212634/https://www.t13.cl/noticia/elecciones-2021/tendencias/pedro-pascal-apoyo-gabriel-boric-elecciones-segunda-vuelta-23-11-2021 |url-status=live |language=es}}</ref>

==Acting credits and accolades==
{{main|Pedro Pascal on screen and stage}}
Beginning his career in 1996, Pascal's highest rated film and television projects, according to the review aggregate site Rotten Tomatoes, include: ''The Uninvited'' (2024), ''[[The Last of Us (TV series)|The Last of Us]]'' (2023–present), ''[[If Beale Street Could Talk (film)|If Beale Street Could Talk]]'' (2018), ''[[Calls (TV series)|Calls]]'' (2021), ''[[The Good Wife]]'' (2009–2011), ''[[The Mandalorian]]'' (2019–present), ''[[Prospect (film)|Prospect]]'' (2018), ''[[Narcos]]'' (2015–2017), ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' (2014), and ''[[Graceland (TV series)|Graceland]]'' (2013–2014).<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/celebrity/pedro_pascal |title=Pedro Pascal – Rotten Tomatoes |date=May 20, 2024 |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |access-date=May 20, 2024 }}</ref>

